*Total tunnel length from the Innsbruck bypass to Fortezza/Franzensfeste: {{convert|64|km|mi|3|abbr=on}}
*Length from the Innsbruck portal to the Fortezza/Franzensfeste portal: {{convert|55|km|mi|3|abbr=on}}
*Diameter of each of the single-track tubes: {{convert|8.1|m|ft|abbr=on}}
*Distance between cross passage tunnels: {{convert|333|m|ft|abbr=on}}
*Elevation at highest point: {{convert|794|m|ft|abbr=on}}
*Maximum [[overburden]]: {{convert|1720|m|ft|abbr=on}}<ref name="urlwww.tunneltalk.com" />
*Start of construction: 1999 (preparations), 2007 (exploratory section), 2011 (main tunnel)
*End of construction: 2032
*Total cost: [[Euro|€]]8.384 billion 
*Electrification System:
**[[15 kV AC railway electrification|15&nbsp;kV 16.7 Hz AC]] (Austrian side) <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cifi.it/download/il-tunnel-di-base-del-brennero-bbt-progettazione-e-realizzazione-del-collegamento-ferroviario-8-settembre-2025/ |title=Il Tunnel di Base del Brennero (BBT): progettazione e realizzazione del collegamento ferroviario - 8 settembre 2025 |website=cifi.it |access-date=2025-10-14 |publisher=CIFI - Collegio Ingegneri Ferroviari Italiani |language=italian |archive-date=2025-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251012073557/https://www.cifi.it/download/il-tunnel-di-base-del-brennero-bbt-progettazione-e-realizzazione-del-collegamento-ferroviario-8-settembre-2025/ |url-status=live }}</ref>
**[[25 kV AC railway electrification|25&nbsp;kV 50 Hz AC]] (Italian side)
*Control and command system: [[European Train Control System#Level 2|ETCS Level 2]]
*Operating speed: {{convert|250|km/h|mi/h|0|abbr=on}} for passenger trains and {{convert|160|km/h|mi/h|0|abbr=on}} for freight trains

